		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Fan Faire II Panel Report</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=412007" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    Everlore Editor, Umbo has written a report of one of the discussion panels regarding the Future of EverQuest and Sony/Verant. Here is a excert:
<blockquote>
<p>
Character server moves: The biggest problem Verant has with character moves is how it effects the economy. This is with cash, equipment, and legendary items. To this end they are investigating the possibility of allowing players to move their own characters around to different servers as long as they bring NOTHING with them. No comment was made if these moves would be single character moves or if it would move all your characters between the two servers.
</p>
</blockquote>
<p>
Head over and check out the <a  href="http://www.everlore.com/viewarticle.asp?ID=412004">complete report</a>!</p>

		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
